1 unit Cheese Pizza
1 unit Pepperoni Pizza

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees.

Remove pizzas from box and plastic wrapping.

Place pizzas on a baking sheet (depending on the size of your sheet, you may need to use two). Bake on middle rack until cheese melts and crusts are golden brown, 12-14 minutes if frozen or 10-12 minutes if thawed.

Remove sheet from oven and let pizzas cool for 2 minutes before serving.